HEADWORD: Whirlicote
<hw>Whirl"i*cote</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An open car or
chariot.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of old time coaches were not known in this island, but chariots,
or <qex>whirlicotes</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Stow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whirligig</ent>⟦br⟧
